      "narrative": {
        "News": "France - TotalEnergies - Normandy: the 57,000 bpd catalytic re- former and two 40,100 bpd gas oil hydrotreaters were restarted during the evening of July 1. Also, increased activity continued at the 55,600 bpd hydrocracker since June 29, but remained below normal operational levels thus far. The 205,600 bpd CDU was re- cently restarted on June 29. All monitored units were shut during afternoon of June 26 as result of a reported power outage. Netherlands - Shell - Rotterdam: elevated flaring began at the refinery during the late evening of July 1. Activity at all monitored units remained unchanged.",
        "Ongoing Events": "France - TotalEnergies - Donges: increased activity began at the 220,000 bpd CDU, 97,000 bpd VDU and the 40,000 bpd VGO hy- drotreater during the evening of June 30, but remained below nor- mal operational levels thus far. The crude section was shut on May 9 and the VGO hydrotreater was shut on April 26. The 55,000 bpd FCC and the 39,000 bpd visbreaker remained off- line. Planned work was expected to begin early May, according to sources. Netherlands - BP - Rotterdam: the 62,000 bpd FCC was restar- ted during the afternoon of June 30. Increased activity began dur- ing the morning of June 29. The unit was shut on June 25. Also, the 35,000 bpd naphtha hydrotreater was shut on June 24 and re- mained offline. Germany - Klesch - Heide: increased activity began at the 20,300 bpd catalytic reformer during the evening of June 25, but remained below normal operational levels thus far. Decreased activity began at the unit on May 20 and the unit went offline on May 28.",
        "Planned Maintenance": "France - TotalEnergies - Donges: unspecified planned work is expected to start in May, according to source. Germany - MiRO - Karlsruhe: planned work on the FCC is ex- pected during the spring of 2027, according to Bloomberg."
      }
