      "narrative": {
        "News": "No changes since last report.",
        "Ongoing Events": "Italy - Saras - Sarroch: the 26,500 bpd gasoline hydrotreater was shut during the late morning of June 30. Significant decreased activity began at that time. Spain - BP - Castellon: the 3,500 bpd alkylation unit was shut during the afternoon of June 30. Significant decreased activity and elevated flaring began at that time. Spain - Moeve - Huelva: the 120,000 bpd CDU and the 40,000 bpd VDU were shut during the evening of June 29. Signi- ficant decreased activity and gradual cooling began at that time. Italy - ENI - Milazzo: the 111,000 bpd CDU was shut at approxim- ately 14:28 (GMT) June 26. Significant decreased activity began at that time. The 12,000 bpd catalytic reformer was shut during the evening of June 21. Significant decreased activity began at that time. The unit was recently shut on June 16 and restarted on June 18. France - INEOS - Lavera: the 240,000 bpd CDU and the 33,500 bpd gas oil hydrotreater were restarted during the morning of June 24. The units were shut on June 21. Also, the 36,500 bpd FCC was shut on June 15 and remained offline. Spain - Repsol - Cartagena: a hydrogen plant was restarted dur- ing the morning of February 13 following a brief outage. The unit was shut on February 11. Also at the refinery, the 100,000 bpd CDU was shut during the evening of January 26 and remained off- line.",
